  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Every project contains some measure of uncertainty. The Risk Management&amp;nbsp;practice deals with this uncertainty,&#xD;
    trying to understand its&amp;nbsp;potential influence on the project, such as the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../practice.mgmt.risk_mgmt.base-ibm/guidances/termdefinitions/risk_consequence_cost_9809DA16.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_QQuZEOt-Ed-sPcqWan6Daw&quot;>risk consequence cost&lt;/a>. Throughout the project, the project manager, team, and&#xD;
    stakeholders&amp;nbsp;are involved in identifying and prioritizing risks, proposing strategies to respond to them, and&#xD;
    monitoring&amp;nbsp;the events that might trigger the risks to happen.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <additionalInfo>&lt;p>&#xD;
    For more information on practices,&amp;nbsp;see the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ibm.com/developerworks/rational/practices/&quot;&#xD;
    target=&quot;_blank&quot;>practices resource page&amp;nbsp;on IBM&amp;reg; DeveloperWorks&amp;reg;&lt;/a>.&#xD;
&lt;/p></additionalInfo>
  <problem>The purpose of this practice is to guide a project team in identifying and managing risks.</problem>
  <goals>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The goal in performing this practice is to increase the probability and impact of positive events and decrease the&#xD;
    probability and impact of events adverse to the project [&lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithUserText&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../../core.mgmt.common.base/guidances/supportingmaterials/references.mgmt_D80619F3.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_JlTPUM6aEdyuBO4ZIzcyig&quot;>PMI&lt;/a>].&#xD;
&lt;/p></goals>
